sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser as Browser (SPA)
    participant Django as Django Backend
    participant Cognito as AWS Cognito
    participant IdP as IdP (Entra ID)
    participant PostAuth as PostAuthFederationLink Lambda
    participant PreToken as PreTokenGeneration Lambda

    Note over Browser,PreToken: Migration — first SAML login. User not yet in Cognito.<br/>IdP configs already synced to Cognito (see one-time sync job).

    Note over Browser: Generate PKCE pair:<br/>code_verifier = random(32 bytes base64url)<br/>code_challenge = BASE64URL(SHA256(code_verifier))<br/>state = random nonce<br/>Store in sessionStorage: state + code_verifier

    Browser->>Django: GET /api/auth/discovery<br/>?email=user@example.com&state=nonce<br/>&code_challenge=Z&code_challenge_method=S256<br/>&redirect_uri=callback_url&client_id=X
    Note over Django: Look up IdP provider by email domain<br/>Build Cognito /oauth2/authorize URL<br/>with identity_provider=EntraSaml + all PKCE params
    Django-->>Browser: 302 Location: /oauth2/authorize?identity_provider=EntraSaml&response_type=code&state=nonce&code_challenge=Z&...

    Browser->>Cognito: GET /oauth2/authorize?identity_provider=EntraSaml&...
    Note over Cognito: Validate client + redirect_uri<br/>Look up EntraSaml provider<br/>Build SAML AuthnRequest
    Cognito-->>Browser: 302 Location: https://login.microsoftonline.com/...?SAMLRequest=...

    Browser->>IdP: GET (redirect to IdP login page)
    Note over IdP: User enters credentials<br/>IdP validates identity
    IdP->>Cognito: POST /oauth2/idpresponse (SAMLResponse)
    Note over Cognito: Validate SAML assertion + signature<br/>Extract email from attribute mapping<br/>Create federated Cognito user<br/>Generate authorization code
    Cognito-->>Browser: 302 Location: callback_url?code=AUTH_CODE&state=nonce

    Note over Browser: Assert state == sessionStorage.federated_auth_nonce

    Browser->>Cognito: POST /oauth2/token<br/>grant_type=authorization_code&code=AUTH_CODE<br/>&redirect_uri=callback_url&client_id=X&code_verifier=VERIFIER
    Note over Cognito: Verify code_verifier against stored code_challenge<br/>Trigger PostAuthentication Lambda
    Cognito->>PostAuth: PostAuthentication event<br/>userAttributes={email, sub, identities:[{providerType:SAML, providerName:EntraSaml}]}

    Note over PostAuth: _is_federated_login() = true<br/>Extract email + Cognito sub
    PostAuth->>Django: GET /api/internal/user-lookup/?email=user@example.com
    Django-->>PostAuth: 200 {"id":42,"email":"user@example.com"}
    PostAuth->>Django: POST /api/internal/link-cognito/<br/>{"django_user_id":42,"cognito_user_id":"sub-uuid","email":"user@example.com"}
    Django-->>PostAuth: 200 {"linked":true}
    PostAuth->>Cognito: AdminUpdateUserAttributes custom:django_id="42"

    Note over Cognito: Trigger PreTokenGeneration before issuing tokens
    Cognito->>PreToken: PreTokenGeneration event<br/>userAttributes={email, sub, identities:[SAML]}<br/>(custom:django_id absent — snapshot taken before PostAuth write)
    Note over PreToken: _login_method() returns "saml" + "EntraSaml"
    PreToken->>Django: POST /api/internal/login-access-check/<br/>{"email":"user@...","login_method":"saml","provider_name":"EntraSaml"}
    Django-->>PreToken: 200 {"allowed":true,"django_id":"42"}
    Note over PreToken: django_id="42" received in access-check response.<br/>No separate resolve-django-id call needed.
    PreToken-->>Cognito: claimsToAddOrOverride={django_id:"42"}

    Cognito-->>Browser: 200 {id_token, access_token, refresh_token}
    Note over Browser: SAML login complete. Tokens stored.
